==Japanese==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Hiragana]]: [[つじぎり]]
*[[Romaji]]: [[tsujigiri]], [[tuzigiri]]

===Etymology===
[[辻]] (tsuji) “street” + [[斬リ]] (kiri), from [[斬る]] (kiru) “cut, murder”.

===Noun===
'''[[辻]][[斬]]り'''

# The killing of a passerby on the road at night, in order to test the sharpness of a sword, or to improve one’s skill.

[[Category:Japanese nouns|つしきり]]